		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Poison pill</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about business strategy.  For the literal meaning, see <a href="/wiki/Suicide_pill" title="Suicide pill">Suicide pill</a>.</div>
<p><b>Poison pill</b> is a term referring to any strategy, generally in <a href="/wiki/Business" title="Business">business</a> or <a href="/wiki/Politics" title="Politics">politics</a>, to increase the likelihood of negative results over positive ones for a party that attempts any kind of takeover. It derives from its original meaning of a literal poison pill carried by various <a href="/wiki/Espionage" title="Espionage">spies</a> throughout history, taken when discovered to eliminate the possibility of being interrogated for the enemy's gain.</p>
